[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_hecwu")
reagent_id = "CaCl2"
title = "Calcium chloride"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CaCl₂[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]111 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
Ca + Cl₂ → CaCl₂  
Ca + 2HCl → CaCl₂ + H₂  
Ca(OH)₂ + 2HCl → CaCl₂ + 2H₂O  
CaO + 2HCl → CaCl₂ + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of calcium and chloride ions.
• Highly soluble in water.
• Dissolving in water releases heat (exothermic reaction).
• Absorbs moisture from air (hygroscopic).
[b]Where calcium chloride is found[/b]
• Present in seawater.
• Produced as a byproduct in some industrial processes.
[b]Uses[/b]
• De-icing roads in winter.
• Used as a drying agent (desiccant).
• Used in food processing and industry.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can irritate skin and eyes.
Should be handled carefully in concentrated form."
